WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:06.596
Once up a time, there were three -
how shall l put this? - geeks.

00:06.673 --> 00:10.609
Three more unlikely heroes there never were.

00:13.680 --> 00:16.808
We defend the defenseless.
l don't see any other way.

00:16.883 --> 00:20.546
lt wasn't long before their naiveté
nearly got them killed,

00:20.653 --> 00:22.951
so they hooked up with an FBl agent...

00:23.023 --> 00:26.015
That's why we like you.
Your ideas are weirder than ours.

00:26.126 --> 00:29.994
and began publishing a - what shall
l call it? - rag called The Lone Gunman.

00:30.063 --> 00:34.124
The guys at the NSA and the ClA tremble
every time we put out one of these babies.

00:34.200 --> 00:39.399
From their cramped basement office,
they pointed fingers at powerful evil forces.

00:39.506 --> 00:41.633
And some not so evil.

00:41.708 --> 00:46.077
ln their own unique way, the three Gunmen
were patriots, fighting the good fight.

00:46.179 --> 00:50.343
- We tell the stories others refuse to tell.
- That's one way to put it.

00:50.717 --> 00:55.848
And provided expertise
for their friends at the FBl.

00:56.222 --> 00:57.314
She's hot.

00:57.390 --> 01:02.384
For a brief time, it looked as if they might
make a difference in this cold, cruel world.

01:02.495 --> 01:05.055
They acquired an intern
who believed in them.

01:05.165 --> 01:08.498
Let's fight for lost causes. l wanna help.

01:08.568 --> 01:12.504
And a powerful, beautiful nemesis,

01:12.572 --> 01:15.166
who became an ally.

01:15.241 --> 01:17.709
But the world is not kind to idealists,

01:17.777 --> 01:22.771
and those who fight the good fight
don't always win.

